# docs/testing Guidelines

When adding or changing tests, follow [`docs/testing/JOURNEYS.md`](docs/testing/JOURNEYS.md). It is the canonical user-journey catalogue for E2E coverage.

## Journey catalogue (`JOURNEYS.md`)

Each row must include: **ID**, **Name**, **User Type**, **Entry URL**, **Expected Outcome**, **Spec** (exact spec file path).

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Stable IDs | Never renumber `J001`–`J026`; new journeys get the next free ID (`J027`, …). |
| New journey | Add one table row **before or with** the Playwright spec; reference the real file path. |
| Removed journey | Delete or merge the row when the test is removed; do not leave stale IDs. |
| Spec paths | Use repo paths, e.g. `apps/chat-frontend/e2e/journey-chat.spec.ts` (not legacy `frontend/e2e/…`). |

## Implementing journey tests

- Place chat UI journeys under `apps/chat-frontend/e2e/journey-{chat,documents,admin}.spec.ts`.
- Name tests so they map clearly to a journey ID (comment or test title: `J027 — …`).
- One journey per user-visible outcome; do not fold unrelated flows into one ID.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — new journey documented and implemented together
// docs/testing/JOURNEYS.md: | J027 | Export chat transcript | Anonymous | `/` | Download starts | apps/chat-frontend/e2e/journey-chat.spec.ts |
test("J027 export chat transcript", async ({ page }) => { /* … */ });

// ❌ BAD — spec added with no JOURNEYS.md row
test("export works", async ({ page }) => { /* … */ });
```

## Before finishing test work

- [ ] `docs/testing/JOURNEYS.md` updated if journeys were added, renamed, or removed.
- [ ] Spec column points at the file that actually contains the test.
- [ ] IDs are stable and sequential for new journeys only.

If `apps/chat-frontend/e2e/USER_JOURNEYS.md` exists, keep its journey list consistent with `docs/testing/JOURNEYS.md`.
